We calculate the number of cases by the following formula;
1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$x_i = \alpha _i P_i^ + + \beta _i P_i^ - \left( {i = 1, \ldots ,6} \right){\text{ }}$$\end{document} where
irisk group index (i = 1,…,6)xithe number of cases from ith risk group. i = 1,…,6αithe probability of being influenza if taken preventive vaccination at risk group i. i = 1,…,6βithe probability of being influenza if not taken preventive vaccination at risk group i. i = 1,…,6 (We assumed that it is equal to gross attack rate)Pi+the number of people from risk group i who take preventive vaccination.Pi−the number of people from risk group i who do not take preventive vaccination

The following equation can be written as;
2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_i^ - + P_i^ + = G_i {\text{ for }}i = 1, \ldots ,6.$$\end{document}where
Githe number of people in risk group i

Many workers need bed rest during the pandemic influenza and it will cause the lost of workdays. We calculate the cost of lost workdays (C
lw) by multiplying the estimated number of workdays missed by the average daily minimum wage for each individual.
3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{lw} = mwd * dw * qwf$$\end{document}Where
mwdaverage number of workdays missed due to pandemic influenzadwaverage daily minimum wage (US$)qwfquantity of workforce affected from influenza

The quantity of workforce from affected from influenza is equal to the following sum;
4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$qwf = x_2 + x_3 + x_4 + x_5 $$\end{document}
x
1 and x
6 has not been included in eq. (4), because x
1 denotes the number of sick people aged under 18 years, and x
5 denotes the number of sick people aged over 65 years. These two groups of people are generally outside the workforce. The daily minimum wage is approximately 18 US$ in Turkey hence this value is used for dw value in the calculations.

Total cost consists of the sum of direct healthcare costs and indirect costs.
5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{av} = \sum\limits_{i = 1}^m {P_i^ + } * vc + \sum\limits_{i = 1}^m {x_i } * av_i $$\end{document}
6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{icu} = \sum\limits_{i = 1}^m {x_i * p_{icu} * dc_{icu} * d_{icu} } $$\end{document}
7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{n - icu} = \sum\limits_{i = 1}^m {x_i } * p_{n - icu} * d_{n - icu} * dc_{n - icu} $$\end{document}
8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$C_{vu} = \sum\limits_{i = 1}^m {x_i } * p_{vu} * d_{vu} * dc_{vu} $$\end{document}
9\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$TC = C_{av} + C_{icu} + C_{n - icu} + C_{vu} + C_{lw} $$\end{document}where
vcunit cost of preventive vaccine (US$/person)aviunit cost of antiviral treatment for risk group i (US$)Cavtotal cost of vaccination and antiviral treatment (US$)Cicutotal cost of ICU-care (US$)Cn-icutotal cost of non-ICU care (US$)Cvutotal cost of ventilator usage (US$)picuthe rate of ills which need ICU care (%)pn-icuthe rate of ills which need non-ICU care (%)pvuthe rate of ills which need ventilators (%)dcicuunit cost of ICU-care (US$/day)dcvuunit cost of ventilator usage (US$/day)dcn-icuunit cost of non-ICU care (US$/day)dicuaverage length of ICU hospital stay for influenza-related illness (days)dn-icuaverage length of non-ICU hospital stay for influenza-related illness (days)dvuaverage length of ventilator usage for influenza-related illness (days)TCtotal cost (US$)mthe number of risk groups
